body:
@nietras Thanks for writing up the [proposal](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2742#issuecomment-571570024). In the upcoming 1.2 release (early March), we plan on separating the managed assembly into a separate package called Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.Managed. Each execution provider will be delivered in it's own separate package *without* the managed assembly. This aligns with your proposal partially. 

At this time we do not plan to separate the pdb files and x86/linux/mac binaries into separate packages for the sake of simplicity of our first party users.

xref: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2184
